inn1.comm: 131 kph, starts with a ginger loosener that wafts away wide of off stump and Watto leaves
fuller and straighter, on the pads and Watto works it carefully to the leg side
lively stuff from Mpofu and the first appeal of the day, he jags this one in bigtime off the seam and it raps Watto on the pads as he pushes down the line. Was surely headed down the leg side
yes, no, may be, yes, surely. Ok. Watson is away with a single they eventually take. Back of a length outside off, he leans back and steers behind point for one
short ball, angled into Haddin's body and he stands tall to nudge behind square for his first World Cup run
slower ball to end the over, back of a length outside off, Watto reaches out cautiously and defends into the covers
speared on the pads, worked away to the leg side
again flat and fast on leg stump, turned away square for a single. What can Watto do
armer now, Price is already chirping away! Watson plays back and manages to keep it out
slides this one down the leg side, and it is called a wide. Taibu collects cleanly.
flat but a bit of turn as this straightens from outside off, Watto stays back and defends down the line
this one drifts onto the pads, Watson glances behind square for a single
hustling start from Price, another tight delivery coming in very quickly, Haddin covers the line and defends
and Mpofu bowls a shocker, angled generously down the leg side, Watson glances it happily along to fine leg for four
better, gets the inducker to start from outside off and it jars in towards the leg stump line. Watson works it square and a fumble from Utseya gives away the single
keeps this outside off and Haddin defends compactly into the off side
fuller length, on middle and leg, it was there for the on drive, but Haddin played it straight to mid on
on middle and leg again in the low 130s, Haddin gracefully tucks it square for another single.
135 kph, but that came off the track slower than Watson expected as he shaped to cut. Not much room either and he ended up bottom edging it away to the off side
hint of flight from Price, on leg stump and it is driven towards long on for one
back of a length, flat and quick, Watto gets half forward and defends
very tight line. "WHAtaaa line!," yells Taibu, Watson again covers the line and defends
for variety, he slows one up and Watto defends to the on side of the pitch. Price fumbles as he tumbles and gives away one
this time Price fields off his own bowling, diving away to his right and Taibu shouts his appreciation!
ends with a single as Haddin reaches out and turns the wrists to get a single to square leg
straightish line and Haddin puts it away for a single through midwicket
quiet andcareful start from Aus. Fuller length, it was there for the drive, Watson got forward nicely but chose to check drive towards mid off
short of good length outside off, Watson hangs back and forces it towards cover point
another good inducker from Mpofu, at polite pace. Watson did not account for the movement as he shaped into the forward defensive and it hit pad, but was headed down the leg side.
fuller length, on the perfect line just outside off, Watson covers the line and defends
good finish to the over, slower ball on a length outside off, Watson stays on the backfoot and punches into the covers
quick delivery coming in with the arm from outside off, defended by Haddin
fuller, gets Haddin to come forward and defend again
strays onto the pads and Haddin works him through midwicket for a single
smart shot from Watson, waiting for the ball to come on and turning the wrists enough to beat short midwicket for another single
more air than normal, Haddin tries to deflect with the angle towards square leg, but can't find the gap
good tight stuff here, Price keeps it on middle and off, just short of driving length and Haddin defends compactly

well bowled Mpofu, slips in a near-perfect yorker on leg stump, but he doesn't have the extra pace. Watson did not expect it, and managed to jam the bat down and squeeze it away to mid on for a hustled single
back of a length outside off and Haddin defends into the off side

whoa Watto, don't try to steal singles from that pocket dynamo Tatenda! Haddin looks to dab a delivery outside off, and it goes nowhere. Taibu runs up and swoops on it and has a go, but misses the stumps. Watson had to fly to make his ground
angling in towards the pads, Watson gets the front foot across and works it to square leg.
slower delivery that, the offcutter, Watson spotted it and focused on keeping it out safely. Defended to the leg side
back of a length, Watson just gets behind the line to defend to the leg side
Price bustles away, fast and angled in towards middle and leg, Haddin can't get it away
slows this one up, Haddin looks to sweep but can't beat the man at short fine
length ball, no spin on middle and leg, Haddin defends down the track

that's the sort of shot that makes you wonder why Haddin doesn't have a better average. Superb footwork, just backs away an imperceptible foot to the leg side, and hence is in position to drive Price against the spin. He unfurls the most pleasing of cover drives and it slithers away to the fence.
gets the single this time as Price flattens the length
on Watto's pads, he closes the face of the bat and picks up a single through midwicket
Mpofu gets the offcutter going again, from outside off and Watto defends down the track. That's his 17th dot ball in 4.1 overs
make that 18. Fuller length outside off, Watson plays that trademark on a knee squarish cover drive, but without power
another offcutter this time ends on the pads and Watson easily clips it behind square for a single
that touch of inward nip again, Haddin hangs back and tries to get inside the line and work it to the leg side. Can't get a single though
over-pitched outside off, Haddin deals with it without violence, leaning out and pushing it through mid off for a single
over-pitched slower ball, Watson presses out into the drive with more power this time, but straight to mid off
Price lands this on leg stump, Haddin works it square straight to the man at square leg
straighter this time, again worked off the pads and cut off backward of square leg
back of a length on off stump, Hadidn stays back and defends
and again, why so defensive? Haddin blocks a delivery on leg stump to the leg side. Price shares his dinner plans with Watson. Watson doesn't like it. Aha!
there's no intent for a single here, Haddin again covers the line and blocks.
finally Haddin gets a single, works it wide of mid on for a single. What a dawdle.
flight! On middle and off, Haddin reaches out and defends
slightly shorter length, Haddin stays back this time and defends
leans out and gets to the flight to defend again. Three men in the deep on the leg side
another yes-no situation, Haddin works him with the spin off the pads to square leg. He runs, Watto doesn't. He stops, Watto charges. All order restored in the end.
maiden for Utseya, Haddin stays back and check-drives the last ball to the leg side
flat and fast, Watson stays back and punches through mid on for a single
Haddin plays off the front foot, defends to the leg side
slows one in the air for a change, Haddin is nearly foxed as he presses forward early. Defence to the leg side
finally Haddin gets the single, on drive through widish mid on and the strike rotates
speared in onto middle and leg again, Watson drives cautiously to long on for another single
hint of turn away from the right hander, he comes forward and pushes with the spin into the covers
flighted on middle and leg, worked off the pads to midwicket
outside off this time, Watson drives into the covers. Can't get the gap. Watson gets a change of bats.
full length outside off, Watto plays back to it and defends down the track.
Single! Celebrate. Full outside off, Watto drives into the covers and surprise, surprise - he finds the gap
on Haddin's pads, he works it to the leg side. No run

Ah, what happened there? One of those rare occasions when the ball hit the stumps without disturbing the bails, I reckon. Replays awaited. Flat and turning in from Utseya, Haddin was keen to work it to the leg side, he played all around it as opened his stance and looked to flick. It ran off the inside edge, between his legs and hits the base of the leg stump. The bail stays put. Haddin smiles, Taibu moans. Some excitement after 13 quiet overs.
116 kph, rare loose delivery from Mpofu. In fact, just his second in the day as he delivers the full offcutter on leg stump. Once again, Watson tucks in with a flick through square leg

finally Australia realise this is not the World Test Championship. Mpofu bangs a short, friendly offcutter and Watson cracks the pull shot with the kind of fluency he showed in the Ashes. No one had a chance as it flew away well in front of square
back of a length and very close to off, the patent on one knee steer to third man from Watson.

Haddin opens up now. He set himself up for the drive as he took a step out of the crease, but Mpofu kept it short of the length. That did not deter Haddin, who just extended the arms and swat-dragged it over wide mid on. Clean hit
Mpofu responds with a bouncer, Haddin was charging again, but decided to back out of the shot

silky smooth and slick from Haddin as Australia get 17 off the over. Back of a length, in fact too short outside off. It was there for cross-batted brutalisation through the off side, but Haddin decided to deal with finesse. He just waved the wand through the line, the way Damien Martyn would have and sends it away over the covers for four
very fill and straight, Watson drives past the bowler for a single
ah, Hadiin drives in the same direction as Utseya dives into Watson as he looks to stop it. Most people can't find a way past Watson. Utseya doesn't either. Single down the ground
full outside off, driven into the off side

lovely fielding from Ervine, saves four runs for his side. Tossed up outside off, Haddin drives against the spin and it seems headed for the cover boundary. Ervine goes completely horizontal as he runs from mid off and dives, and collects cleanly with the left arm. Not even a single in the end.
bunts the last delivery to the leg side for a single
flat and quick on off stump, punched to the off side and Price charges away to his left to stop it
flat again, on the pads, Haddin works it straight to square leg
this time he gets the single, working it off the pads for one
Watson now, hangs back in the crease and deflects through square leg for a single
tossed up outside off, Haddin leans out and drives past the bowler for a single
tossed up on middle and leg, worked with the spin through midwicket.
on off stump this time, Haddin works it back towards the bowler
flat and fast on off stump, Haddin hangs back and defends to mid on
tossed up slowly, Haddin reaches across and works it with the spin to midwicket
back of a length this time, Haddin hangs back and defends down the track
and again, Utseya gets his second maiden in, haddin stays in the crease and defends
tossed up leggie on leg stump, driven past the bowler to long on for one
again, tossed up and driven down the track, hits the stumps at the bowler's end. Doesn't touch the bowler's hand and Watson was in, in any case
nice stuff, the flat delivery that goes on without spinning. Skids into the pads of Haddin, surprised as he is caught on the crease
slower through the air on leg stump, this time he gets the single by flicking through square leg
lands this too far down the leg side, and since he isn't Warne, it doesn't rip out and hit the stumps. The batsman facing isn't Gatting either. Wide called.
again on leg stump, Watson works it square for another single
back of a length on leg stump, defended down the track.
tossed up on off, Watto reaches out and smothers the spin
short of a length, Watto pounces on the back foot and cuts, but can't find the gap
again Watto tries to stay back and work through the off side but can't get it away
what's that, an arm ball? Surely went the other way, but that was too short to trouble Watto who punches into the off side

Zimbabwe's first ever referral now. Utseya lands this back of a length outside off and it comes in gently with the angle, and then sharply with the spin. Haddin looks to work it through square leg, casually off the back foot, and is hit in front of middle. It was hitting middle and leg. Not sure why Asoka de Silva said not out. The third umpire overturns the verdict. Zimbabwe have struck.
another overspinner from Utseya, holds its line on off stump, and Ponting cautiously plays it to the leg side
Cremer lands this outside the leg stump and he deflects it fine. Two extras
full and straight, on middle stump, Watto doesn't have to reach out to smother this one
Watto presses forward gets to the spin and plays through the leg side
compacto Watto. Full on middle and leg, he just gets evertything behind it and defends
Watto gets a single this time, through the leg side and Ponting has strike
Ponting is away, full on leg stump, driven through wide mid on for one
half shout! Ponting almost does a Haddin, but think he got bat on this before it hit the pads as he played back to an offie. Hmm.
full delivery outside off, Pontind drives through the covers for one
Watto tries to whip with the spin through midwicket, but can't get it away
flatter, Watto plays back and forces it through wide mid on for one
Ponting gets a single this time, hanging on the crease, using the wrists and working it through midwicket
turning down the leg side, Haddin works it squarer this time for one
aired up by Cremer, on the pads, on driven through mid on for a single
tossed up on off and driven into the covers for one
slows it up through the air, Watto leans out and defends solidly. If I had a dime each time that was done today.
tossed up on middle and off, Watto defends again.
yes you guessed right. Forward defensive again.
tossed up outside off, driven into the covers for one more
Utseya throws it up on off stump, driven down to long on for one
Price at point, prancing and prowling. Ponting can't get the single away as he steers backward of point
defends into the off side this time.
Ponting gets a single away down the ground. Over to Watto
Watto has hit four. Stop the press. Cherish the moment. Short ball from Utseya, how rare is that? Watto swat-pulls down the ground for four. Rafael Nadal would have been proud of the shot.
another short one, Watto doesn't get enough power behind it this time, and gets a single down the ground
Watson gets a single away, staying back and playing with the spin
extra spin from Cremer, Pontin looks to get forward and defend and it runs away off the outside half backward of square
Ponting goes over the top and almost holes out. Tossed up outside off and Ponting looks to play the inside out extra cover drive. It almost carries to Chakabva patrolling the extra cover fence.
Watson hangs deep in the crease and works it behind square for a single
delicate from Ponting, gets his front foot inside the line and deflects a ball straying down the leg side down to fine leg for three
Watson stays back and forces a delivery outside off stump down to long on for a single
turning in from a length, outside off, swatted down the ground for a single
nice placement from Ponting, stays back to a short of length ball that did not offer much width for the cut, but he guided it expertly into the covers for a couple
Ponting's class could break the shackles here. He stays back, waits for the ball to turn in and runs it almost out of Taibu's gloves down to third man. You need pedigree to play these shots.
fuller length on off stump, Watson reaches out and drives through mid off for one more
Ponting forces him with the spin, off the back foot through midwicket
Watson enters the nervous 50s. Stays back to a shockingly short ball outside off and sends it packing through the covers. Nicely played, and it's crucial that he keeps going
tossed up on off stump, Ponting presses forward and drives through wide mid off for a single
flightded on middle and off, he reaches out and plays defensively
another flighted offering on the stumps, Ponting tries to force it away through the leg side, but can't get it away
another dot, Ponting looks to sweep and misses as it slides down onto the pads. Four dots on the trot
finally Ponting gets a single away, working against the spin through the leg side
Watson comes forward to another slow loopy delivery on leg stump and defends down the track
slips the first ball down the leg
angled into the pads, too easy for Ponting who clips it through midwicket for one
better line, on off stump, Watto defends into the covers.
lovely touch from Watto. Again Elton dangles this one on the pads and Watto gets the front foot across and clips it daintily through square leg for four.

another one on the pads, Watto flicks behind square for one. Zim need to be careful here, they shouldn't let Watto get out of the nervous 50s too soon. Surely they know how many times he's been out in the 50s?
Ponting drives crisply through mid off for one, full length ball and an easy single
full delivery outside off, Watson plays the square drive, uppishly but short of the man at point.
Ponting gets forward to a full delivery on middle and off, punches it down to long on for a single
this one turns away from Watto, who adjusts his forward defensive and plays it away off the outside half
air again from Cremer, Watto punches with the full face of the bat through wide long on for another single
almost fooled Cremer down the leg side. Ponting was advancing, Cremer saw him coming and tried to get a leg side stumping, Ponting adjusted and managed to get a tickle down the leg side. Close

Watto has gone past the nervous 50s in majestic style. Primal violence in that pull, Cremer fed him a gentle half tracker and Watto tried to smash it from the West of India to the East. he got as far as the stands at deep midwicket. Went down on as knee and brutalised it. Bosh.
and he gets a single to retain strike, in front of square
over-pitched on leg stumo, Watto drills it down the ground for one
back of a length outside off, Ponting punches into the covers for another single
Watson this time, drives easily through the off side for a single
Elton holds the length back, Ponting still comes forward, covers the line and drives down the ground with a straight bat. Singles easily available now.
Zimbabwe are releasing the stranglehold now. Another gentle delivery on the pads, Watto happily glances it square for a couple as Coventry comes around to save it

the captain has let his side down here. Another dolly on the toes, Watson twinkles away inside the line and helps it along with better timing, backward of square. Coventry can't do much and it is four more
Ponting skips out, gets to the pitch and clips in down the ground for a single
Watson hangs back in the crease and punches through wide mid on for another single
different strokes for different folks. While Watto hangs back by default, Ponting keeps skipping out of the crease. He drives through mid off this time for another single
nice work from Cremer, Watto looks to force him away through the off side,  but he jumps across and fields
Watson leans out and defends as a delivery turns away from him sharply
ends the over with a single, driving fluently into the covers
he begins with a horribly short delivery straying down the leg side, Watto happily pulls it away behind square. Part-time problems for Zim.
better, gets some drift this time and Watto has to cover the line and defend
Pontins gets inside the line and works a single through midwicket
another short ball, Watto will feel aggrieved he did not get four for it. Hits the leather off the ball as he pulls powerfully to the man in the deep
Ponting comes forward and defends the last ball with the spin into the covers
tossed up on off, Watto gets forward and blocks

huge appeal for lbw, turned down. Will they refer it? Yes, they will. Tossed up on middle and off and fizzing along straight, off the track. Watto was well forward, but the replays suggest that was crashing into middle and off, three-fourths of the way up. No evidence that it hit bat before pad either. Yep, the third umpire helps Umpire Kettleborough overturn it and Zim have got two in two right today.
played off the pads towards deep square leg
Ponting gets behind the line on the back foot and defends to the bowler
played off the back foot towards the off side
played towards cover once again
played through midwicket off the front foot
Ponting comes forward and plays to midwicket but can't find the gap
Ponting comes forward once again and defends with bat and pad close together
defended on the front foot

Ponting's run out by a splendid direct hit from deep midwicket. Clarke came forward to take the ball on the full and flicked it to deep midwicket. The batsmen wanted the second and had Mpofu's throw from the deep not hit the stumps directly at the non-striker's end, they would have got the second. But it did and Zimbabwe's players are delighted.
played towards deep square leg for one more
Clarke comes forward once again and drives to long on for a single
Cremer bowls a tight line and White defends on the front foot
drifts on to leg stump this time and White nudges it around the corner
Clarke waits late for one outside off stump and cuts deftly, Mpofu fields and throws superbly on the boundary once again
played behind square for a single
tossed up on middle stump, played back to the bowler
slightly shorter in length and the batsman plays the ball behind square
defended towards the bowler from the crease
short ball and White could have hit that anywhere on the off side. He chose the fielder at cover
White tries to reverse sweep and fails to connect
driven to long-on for a single
Clarke stays in his crease and flicks the ball off his pads through square leg
Cremer hits the pad with a straighter one as Clarke plays off the back foot but the impact was such that the ball would have missed leg stump
Clarke comes forward and drives the ball hard towards the bowler
a skiddy delivery and Clarke rocks back and pulls to deep square
a wayward slog from White, tried to cart it from wide outside off against the spin towards the leg side, he missed
White drives the ball firmly just wide of a diving Cremer towards long off
played forcefully towards long-on for a single
defended watchfully towards the bowler
played back towards the bowler once again
shorter in length and this time White drives it past the bowler
Clarke strides forward and drives fluently towards long-on
pushed wide of the bowler on the off side for a single
Clarke tries to work the ball on the leg side but fails to make contact this time
another push towards long-on for another single. Australia have the batting Powerplay left to take.
played towards the off side this time
pushed through square leg
tossed up and Clarke gets forward to the pitch of the ball and drives to long-on
played back to the bowler on the front foot
forced towards long-on once again for a single to end the 38th over
forced off the back foot but it's hit towards the bowler
this time it's wide of the bowler and they run a single to long-off
defended on the front foot towards the leg side
played towards mid-on but midwicket cuts it off
eased off the back foot towards long-off for a single. It's the only run-scoring zone at the moment - long on and off.
and again, another single towards long-off
comes down the track and drives towards long-on once again
another delivery payed down the ground
this time it's worked through square leg for a single
width offered outside off and Clarke cuts it in a flash towards the third man boundary. Mpofu picks it up just inside the boundary and sends a rocket of a throw towards Taibu
played through square for a single
quicker ball and the line is pretty straight, played back to the bowler on the back foot
comes down the track to flick but gets a leading edge towards mid-off
full length and White nudges the ball off his boots
short ball and Clarke sends it racing to the deep square boundary with a fierce pull off the back foot
driven towards long-on for a single
played towards deep midwicket for a single
flatter and shorter, nudged off the front foot towards midwicket
pushed off the back foot towards long-on for a single
played towards deep midwicket for one more
White steps out but then has to defend towards midwicket because he is beaten by the length

Ervine had a extremely tough chance at deep midwicket but couldn't take it. White came at Price and lofted the ball towards deep midwicket. Ervine came running off the boundary and dived forward at full stretch. He just got hands to it but couldn't hold on.
played down the ground towards long on
full toss and the batsman pulls hard to Mpofu on the deep square leg boundary. They aren't taking chances against his arm
fired in full and fast outside off stump, White plays it back to the bowler
this time he manages to place it wide of the bowler and collects a single towards long-on
shot, Clarke skips down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball, and lofts cleanly through the line, hitting the ball straight down the ground
shorter ball and Clarke waits in his crease before playing a chippy pull in the air towards deep square leg
White drives the ball with lots of bottom hand, hitting in flat towards long-off. It reaches the fielder after bouncing once.
played towards long off once again, along the ground this time
Clarke went back to pull but the length wasn't that short and the ball hurried on to him. He missed and got struck on the body.
played towards deep square leg for a single
flat and down leg side. White attempts to paddle it past short fine leg but gets hit on the pad
Price fires the ball in at leg stump once again. Clarke can't make contact
Clarke goes back and nudges the ball through square
Clarke tries to make room at first and then gets inside the line as Mpofu strays down leg side. Clarke glances the ball off his hips past short fine leg
short ball down leg side, he will have to re-bowl that.
follows Clarke with a full ball as the batsman makes room to hit over the over side. All the fielders are in the circle on the off side. Clarke can only work it through the leg side this time
White makes a bit of room and biffs the ball down the ground towards long on
full ball down leg side. Mpofu needs to keep it together here.
the slower ball and the batsman mis-times it back to the bowler after trying to make room to hit over the off
another slower ball played behind square
bowled him! White needed to go for it, and he picked a slower ball to try and hit through midwicket. He was early on the shot and the ball cannoned into middle and leg stump off the bottom edge.
lovely delivery on middle stump, no pace to work with on a tight length. Clarke goes back and forces it to cover
driven down the ground for a single
Hussey goes right back and drives the ball from middle stump through cover point
Clarke moves quickly on to the back foot and cuts hard but can't find the gap on the deep point boundary
that is some shot for a second delivery! Hussey gets under the ball and sends it high and far over the bowler's head. Did that clear the sight screen?
played back to the bowler
forced off the back foot towards cover
worked off the pads towards deep square leg
fired down leg side
comes down the track and plays the most awesome cover drive on the move. He's timed and placed it well enough to beat the fielder on the extra-cover boundary
played down the ground for one more
fired down leg side once again, another wide
Clarke makes room to drive a full ball through cover point
Hussey comes forward and drives the ball off his legs towards wide long-on
driven firmly but down the ground to long on where the boundaries are protected
Clarke walks across his crease and flicks the ball off his pads through midwicket
short ball and Clarke plays the pull towards wide long on where the fielder slips after collecting the ball, ensuring that the second run is risk free
terrible ball, full and down leg side, Clarke gets some bat on it to place it wide of a diving Taibu
good length ball outside off, Clarke works it through midwicket and has hit it gently enough to complete the second as the fielder from the deep reaches the ball. That's his half-century too.
expensive over from Zimbabwe. Clarke finishes it by making room to loft a length ball over extra cover. Australia should get 250 now

and that's why! Bowled him! Hussey charges down the track and aims for the heave down the ground. Price drags it shorter, bowls it quicker and keeps it dead straight. Hussey misses by a long way, and Price hits the stumps.
and perhaps this is why. Smith backs away to a flat ball and flat-bats it hard down the ground. He's placed it straight enough to beat long-off
Smith brings up 250 with a superbly executed slow-sweep that sails high and far over deep backward square leg
played towards deep point for a single
dabbed towards short third man
Clarke steps forward and drives towards long-on for a single. Sloppy cricket from Zimbabwe as they concede an over throw

Mpofu is very, very lucky. He bowled a rubbish ball, a full toss on leg stump. Smith could have smashed it, anywhere. Instead he sort of chipped it off his pads and straight to the fielder on the deep square leg boundary.
excellent ball to follow up, a yorker in the blockhole. Clarke digs it out. Such is life. A rubbish ball gets a wicket, an excellent one doesn't.
another full and straight ball, Clarke swings it towards long-on for one
a low full toss outside off stump. Driven powerfully towards long off where a fumble from Coventry allows the second
Johnson lifts the ball with the angle into him and places it into the gap on the deep square leg boundary. That's his zone and Mpofu needs to keep away from it. Full outside off is the way to go.
full toss outside off stump, Johnson swings hard and hits it down the ground towards long on.

inn2.comm: 144kmh, short of a length and straight. Taylor stands tall on the back foot, dabs it towards the off side with soft hands, and calls for the quick single
full and fast but the line is down leg side. Tait doesn't want to be running that long run-up more times than necessary in Indian conditions
short ball this time, outside off stump, Coventry lets it go through to Haddin
good length ball at 143.6 kph outside off stump. Coventry lets it go again
Coventry goes dangerously on to the back foot to a fullish ball that is very straight and defends
Tait grunts as he lets one rip at 145 kph, the length is short and the line is outside off. Coventry shoulders arms
full and wide and Coventry throws his bat at it, aiming to carve it through the point region. Doesn't make contact
full ball angling into the right-hander. Taylor works the ball off his pads towards deep square
shot. Coventry leans into a half-volley outside off stump and sends it racing to the cover boundary with a powerful yet graceful drive
Coventry gets behind the line of a good length ball and defends on the off side. He doesn't move around much in his crease
good length and very straight from Lee. Coventry opens the face and plays the ball towards point
Coventry jumps back to play a short of a length ball and fends it awkwardly, taking his bottom hand off the bat
short of a length and the line is wider outside off stump, Coventry punches off the back foot towards point
short of a length ball angling into the right-hander, Taylor moves back and across and nudges the ball off his hips towards long leg
full ball at 148 kph outside off stump, Taylor takes a small step forward and blocks towards cover
Tait tests Taylor with a bouncer at 145 kph. Taylor sways out of the way and hears the ball whizz past
his hearing needs to be exceptional to hear this one, it is extremely wide outside off
punched off the back foot towards extra cover. More of ball hitting bat than the other way around. He sets off for a single and is home before Ponting's direct hit at the non-striker's end.
Coventry gets on to the back foot and punches a shorter ball through the gap at cover point
Coventry jumps back to defend a good length ball and wants one. Taylor doesn't
full and straight at 137 kph, Taylor gets behind the line and defends
short ball directed at the body. Taylor moves back and across just enough to work the ball behind square
short of a length outside off stump, Coventry barely moves as he lifts his bat out of the way

that is one of the flattest sixes you'll see! Coventry laid into a length ball outside off and played the square drive with immense power. The ball rocketed off the bat and flew over the point boundary. It carried about ten feet over the boundary and smashed into the wall.
fuller length and straighter line, flicked off the pads through square leg
left alone outside off stump
hits a good length with his first ball and is very straight. Coventry defends from his crease on the off side
again there's almost no movement from Coventry. He waits motionless until the ball reaches him and then moves just enough to defend on the off side.
played off the back foot towards point
Johnson pins Coventry on the back foot with a good length delivery. 141.6 kph. Coventry nudges the ball towards the leg side and Johnson runs across to field
a bit too straight this time from Johnson and Coventry turns the ball off his pads towards fine leg
played off the back foot towards cover point
short of a length ball from Lee gets big on Coventry who defends on the leg side. He looks awkward while playing the short ball off the back foot
Coventry attempts to play the pull but was in no control whatsoever. Lee beats him with the short ball
defended from the crease towards the off side

this was a likely dismissal. Coventry was edgy against the short ball and tried to pull this one from outside off stump. The top edge swirled high in the air and the ball descended in the region of silly mid-off, where Lee was waiting to take the caught and bowled
short of a length and very straight. Taibu opens the face and plays towards point
a full ball swings into the right-hander, Taibu plays the drive towards the bowler
Johnson pitches outside leg and Taylor nudges the ball off his pads towards fine leg
full and straight, Taibu stays firm in his crease and plays towards cover
no room to work with and Taibu's attempt to steer towards third man finds backward point
a superb short ball, very straight and intended to hit the body. Taibu does well to watch the ball and sway out of the way
the full one follows the short one. Taibu pushes from his crease towards cover point
worked off the pads towards midwicket
short of a length just outside off stump, Taibu slashes it in the air towards third man
terrific shot, Taylor waits for the short of a length ball outside off and then chips it deftly over the head of the fielder at first slip. He played that so late
short of a length again outside off stump. This one doesn't rise as much so Taylor lets it go
good length with a hint of swing into the right-hander, Taylor defends from his crease
a full ball this time and there's swing into Taylor who mis-times the push towards cover
Taibu plays a crisp square drive off the back foot that nearly pierces the infield. Steve Smith flings himself to his right at point and pulls off a tremendous save
Taylor pushes the ball towards mid-on where Tait, who is perhaps Australia's slowest mover, can't prevent the single
Taibu plays a flashy drive at a good length ball angling across him and edges towards third man
Taylor gets behind the line and defends on the off side
Johnson speeds a good length delivery past the outside edge of Taylor's forward defence
defended solidly off the front foot towards cover
short of a length on leg and middle, Taylor works the ball off his body through the leg side, there's a direct hit from Hussey as Taylor returns for the second but he's safe
Lee pitches on a perfect length on off stump. Taibu defends from his crease towards cover
a touch fuller and Taibu has a real go at a ball he could have put away. The placement of the square drive however isn't good and he hits it to the man at point
slower ball and Taibu plays another drive on the off side
Lee was looking for the yorker and bowled a low and fast full toss. Taibu brings his bat down in time to keep it out
shorter ball and the line is slanting down leg side. Taibu misses the swivel-pull but that's wide
he's placed this! Taibu stands in his crease and slaps a length delivery with power through cover. No feet movement, but excellent timing.
Lee responds with a slower bouncer. Taibu is far too early with his pull shot and gets beaten
good length and very straight. Taylor defends towards the bowler

good length ball and Taylor pushes towards mid-off and takes on Ponting's arm. He doesn't have to worry though but Taibu does. Ponting reaches the ball in a flash and throws at the batsman's end. Taibu dives full length but the throw misses

he's given Watson some catching practice at first slip. Taibu tried to guide the ball towards third man by opening the face but the line of the short of a length ball was far too close to the body. He ended up steering it off the face towards Watson's right. He bent swiftly to take a low catch
left alone outside off stump
Ervine pushes forward at a good length ball that straightens off the pitch and gets beaten outside off. He was a bit late on that shot
defended on the front foot towards point
defended on the front foot towards midwicket

bowled him! Taylor tried to work the ball on the leg side from his crease and closed the face of the bat. He missed and Tait sped the ball through and grazed the pad before uprooting middle stump. Nothing special, just straight, fast and very effective.
full ball on leg stump, Chigumbura gets a bit of pad on the ball and gets a boundary towards fine leg
defended from the crease towards the off
good length ball outside off stump, Chigumbura lets it go
short ball at the body, Chigumbura ducks under it
good length ball outside off stump, pushed off the front foot towards cover point
he's been hit, Ervine lost sight of that short ball and wore it on the grill of the helmet

Johnson bowls a full, fast and straight ball that thuds into Ervine's pads as he tries to play across the line and falls over a touch. Johnson roars an appeal but Asoka de Silva is unmoved, again. Haddin is adamant that it should be reviewed. Replays show that it's pretty plumb. Thank goodness for the UDRS today. Asoka's had a shocker.
another full and straight ball that hits the pad. Johnson appeals but not as convincingly this time. It might have been missing leg so there's no review.
Johnson hits the pad again as Williams tries to work the ball on the leg side. Missing leg again.
defended on the off side on the front foot
Tait strays towards leg again and Chigumbura glances it past a diving Haddin for four towards fine leg
another full ball down leg side, this time there's pad on the ball and Haddin gets some glove on it and slows the pace as it heads towards fine leg
defended on the front foot towards the off side
short of a length ball, Chigumbura defends on the leg side
full length on leg stump, this time Chigumbura can't get the leg glance right and the ball hits his pad
Tait gives Chigumbura some space outside off and he drives a length delivery through extra cover with excellent timing
Johnson ambles in and targets his short balls at the batsman's body. Willaims ducks right under it
Williams stays steady in his crease and plays the square drive through the gap at cover point. Clarke gives chase
Chigumbura gets behind the line of a good length delivery on off and middle and defends with a straight bat towards the bowler
the line is on leg stump and the length a touch shorter. Chigumbura tries to glance the ball off his hips but doesn't make proper contact
defended towards square leg from the crease
Chigumbura chases one that slants across him from over the wicket. The length was there for the drive and Chigumbura went for it and was beaten.
and the outside edge straight away. Nice flight and spin, it breaks away from Williams who feels for it without getting entirely across, it eludes slip and runs away for four
straighter, Williams reaches out and smothers the spin
another edge, this can be frustrating. Williams reaches out and drives without full conviction, and it squeezes away to the right of backward point
a touch of drift and turn away from off stump, Williams leaves
over-pitched on off, Williams drives straight to mid off
flatter and on the pads, Williams looks to flick and misses
back of a length and coming in with the angle, defended to the off side of the pitch
on the pads this time, looks to flick and gets some bat and pad on it away through square leg for a single
back of a length and angling across Williams who defends to the off side off the back foot
similar ball, a touch fuller, similar response from Williams who defends to the off side
very full, on the stumps and this time Williams plays through mid on. Not much feet movement, and Sunny Gavaskar doesn't quite appreciate it, on air.
good start from Watto, Williams opens the face and steers from outside off towards backward point
Krejza drifts in outside off, draws Elton out and he can't get to the pitch and defends to the off side
again skips out, this time he gets to the pitch and works it wide of mid on for a single
Williams continues to defend as Krejza tosses it up
who, where did that come from? Williams has seen enough of Krejza's flight, plonks the front foot down the track and swings him majestically over deep midwicket. Ka-boom.
good response from Krejza, extra turn from middle and off line as Williams leans out, it goes off the outside half towards point
gets closer to the pitch and drives along the ground through mid off for one
Williams hangs back and defends to the off side as Watto angles another one innocously across him
back of a length and on the stumps, Williams flicks in front of square for one more
Elton looks to boom the cover drive away and gets an inside edge as Watto comes on slowly from back of a length.
faster and fuller, Elton motions into the off drive, plays is straight to Ponting at mid off, who fumbles and makes the single easy
full length on middle and leg, Williams looks to flick and gets a leading edge,
Williams retains strike with a push into the covers. It is all very quiet at the moment as the Required rate crosses 6.
prodigious spin from Krejza, drifts into off stump line and then breaks away viciously past the attempted cut. Hmm.
and now one that stays low, Williams gets bat on the cut and picks a single in front of cover point

well played Elton, plays the field to perfection. Tossed up and turning into him from outside off, Elton knew there was a gap at deep extra cover and decided to drive against the spin in the air. Almost went all the way too.
Williams rocks back and cuts despite not having much room, and gets a single to deep point
turns in nicely from outside off, and Elton defends

well, the spin is in. Krejza does a Murali as this breaks in from outside off, changing course as if it is drunk. It beats Elton's drive, beats Haddin, beats everything and goes for four. Big bounce too, took it over the stumps.
back of a length and angling across, Watto will do this all day. Williams defends from the crease
fuller on middle and off, Williams gets half forward and defends compactly
nicely done, back of a length on the pads, Williams controls the whip and redirects it towards deep midwicket for a couple
over-pitched outside off, Williams leans into the drive and gets it out to cover inside the circle
on the pads, Williams works it off the backfoot towards midwicket
effort ball to end the over, Elton had to weave away from it as it went through just outside off
short of a length and straightening from outside off, cut away through cover point for one

Elton's gone. Krejza throws this up well outside off and he goes for the lap-sweep. Too ambitious, he had to bring that around from a long way off, and ended up getting gloving a top edge that popped up on the off side. Haddin runs across and pouches it, then hurries back to effect a stumping, just in case. Elton was already walking away though.
again some big turn from outside off as Regis tries to play through the off side
thrown up well wide outside off and he lets it go. Almost a wide
aha, the ball is stopping on him. Regis tries to go back to a short ball and work it to the leg side with the spin. Ends up playing it too early and almost pops a return catch
fires it in full and from wide of the crease, at 137 kph, Williams hangs in the crease and steers to point
width from Tait, Williams does the smart thing, uses the pace and slaps it backward of square. Sweeper cover runs across and keeps it down to two
full pitched on middle and leg, Williams gets behind the line and defends to the off side
137 kph, he's looking for the yorker, but this one is on the pads and is clipped through square leg for one
over-pitched wide of the crease, Williams jams the bat down on it and steers it square, but straight to the fielder
slightly shorter in length, still Williams looks to drive. He times it well, but straight to point
flighted outside off and straightening, defended down the track by Regis.
short of a length and turning down the leg, worked off the pads through square leg
angled down the leg side, he goes for the sweep and plays it to short fine leg
short ball, turning away from outside off and cut to deep backward point
this one breaks in from outside off, defended off the backfoot to the off side
tossed up outside off, he goes for the bent knee extra cover drive, with a wristy flourish and gets a single to the deep

that's what Tait does best, a Waqar Younisesque thunderbolt straight at the toes, and Regis has no clue where it went after hastily removing his feet from the danger area and stopping the irresistable force. What a yorker.
shortens the length this time, but doesn't reduce the pace, Regis slashes hard. At thin air.
and now the bouncer, some serious pace being worked up, Regis ducks
another short one at 138 kph outside off, Regis weaves out of harm's way
finally gets bat on ball, opens the face and guides it from outside off through backward point

Tait's blown Williams away with 144.7 kph of unplayable pace. Almost a yorker again, from wide of the crease from round the wicket, homes the guided missile in on the line of off stump. Williams has played back to everything, think he'd make a good playback singer. He hangs deep in the crease again and hangs the bat out feebly. It took the edge and flew away at inexplicable pace towards the right of Watto at slip and he does real well to bend down and pluck it low. On second view, it was more a full length ball than a yorker. Still, unplayable.
Utseya drives against the spin into the covers
tossed up outside off, driven thoughtfully into the covers
straightens from off stump, defended down the track
holds the length back and he defends down the track again
this one is turning down the leg and is worked off the pads to the leg side
appeal for lbw, but it was drifting down the leg as he got pad on it, and a leg bye to square leg
short ball outside off, he waits for it and cuts backward of square for a couple
fuller and straighter, defended to the on side of the pitch
shorter outside off, Utseya cuts away in front of square for one
Regis picks a single by forcing a short ball through the covers
another single in front of square to end the over
turns in from outside off, defended off the front foot down the track

Regis perishes to a strange shot, trying to pull a length ball tossed up around middle and leg. He may have played forward to it, he should have played with a straight bat. Instead, he stayed back and looked to pull. It gripped and straightened, whizzed past the bat and thudded into the area above his bent back knee. Plumb.
tossed up outside off, he leans out and smothers the spin.
turning down the leg side, Cremer works it behind square for a single

another huge lbw appeal as Krejza gets one to straighten from off stump, Prosper pushed forward to defend, but it broke back and hit the pad. Not challenged by Aus as umpire Kettleborough says not out
this one doesn't turn so much and Utseya gets bat on it
flat delivery on off, steered off the back foot towards the off side
huge appeal from Haddin, none from anyone else as Smith gets the topspinner going, Cremer jammed the bat down on it at the last moment, and it did not hit pad at all
stays back and works this one off the pads through square leg for one
strange shot, Utseya tries to be cheeky and lap it through short fine leg. Doesn't get it away.
fuller and Utseya drives past cover for a single
Cremer plays the lap shot this time and gets it away for a couple too. Well played, against the spin, but in full control
tossed up from round the wicket and defended
again Utseya gets half forward and blocks down the track
shorter outside off, Utseya stays back and defends
quicker through the air, Utseya adjusts and drives firmly past mid on for a single
tossed up on middle and off, Cremer skips out to the pitch and works it through midwicket
this time he advances and gets to the pitch, drives down the ground for a single
tossed up on off stump and defended with the spin to the off side
this time he gets the single through the covers
gets forward and feebly pushes into the covers.
Utseya drives with the spin into the covers. This game is dawdling along now.
not if Cremer has anything to do with it. He dances out, gets to the pitch and scythes Smith through wide mid on for a boundary
begins with a bouncer outside off from over the wicket, he looks for a upper cut and misses
full and quick on off stump, Utseya drives into the covers
Lee is looking for the yorkers, he's not missing by much. Utseya gets forward and defends down the track
full again, this time Utseya opens the face and drives into the covers for a single
139.6kph, this is why Steyn loves Lee. He can bowl at this speed, at this age. Yorker a foot outside off, he looks to squeeze it away but can't get it away
144 kph. The fastest old bowler in the world. A mini-achievement for Cremer that he got bat on that thunderbolt outside off
the grand old gents are doing well. Ponting now, dives away to his right in cover and stops a single

beaten in the flight, Utseya nearly holes out to White at deep extra cover as he runs in. He was so short of reaching the flight that his edge carried no where and White's run forward and dive did not help.
on the pads, worked to the leg side for a single
Cremer pushes a single into the covers for one
Lee's doing everything except get wickets. Bouncer at 141 kph. Cremer is lucky he didn't suffer bodily harm. Hits something and flies fine for four
very full outside off and driven into the covers, but straight to the covers

for a fleeting moment Cremer did look like Kramer. Full delivery, really pacy and swinging into his pads, Cremer fumbled and stumbled before falling down. It hits the pads and rolls away to the off side
Cremer drives with reasonable fluency as Lee delivers one full outside off
another airy fairy pull as he gets a bouncer at 140 kph. Pops up but lands safely around leg slip. Haddin can't get around in time
another one close to being a yorker, dug out down the track.
played off the pads through square leg for one
played off the back foot towards cover
driven towards long on for a single
nudged towards long on once again
full ball on off stump, driven past the bowler towards long on
forced off the back foot towards long off
short of a length ball over off stump, the batsman shapes up to play it but then takes his bat out of the way rather flamboyantly
left alone outside off stump
full ball on off stump, driven off the front foot towards mid-off. Lee's over-stepped so there's a free-hit coming up
Lee delivers a slower bouncer which Utseya tries to hook and misses
fuller and faster on middle stump, driven towards mid-on from the crease
nudged towards third man for a single
full ball outside off stump, driven off the front foot towards deep point
full ball outside off stump, driven off the front foot towards mid-off and Ponting scores another direct hit at the batsman's end
played from the crease towards the off side
full ball outside off stump, steered towards third man
short ball and Utseya takes evasive action
full toss on middle stump, flicked firmly but straight to the man at midwicket
Tait bowls a fast good-length ball outside off stump and beats the batsman's forward defensive push
played back to the bowler
defended on the front foot
steered towards short third man
pushed down the ground for a single
Utseya strides forward and drives through cover point
played on the off side off the back foot
Utseya uses Tait's pace and dabs a length delivery past Haddin towards the third-man boundary. Deft and well-executed shot.
good length ball on off stump, defended towards the off side from the crease
short of a length ball angling into the right-hander, worked off the hips towards fine leg, Tait's over-stepped so another free-hit coming up
Tait bowls the fast bouncer on the free-hit. Cremer backed away to make room and was then too far away from the ball to play a shot
fuller ball on off stump, driven off the front foot towards cover
short of a length outside off, Cremer slashes and gets a thick edge that flies wide of Haddin for four
full and straight, pushed towards mid-off for a single
driven towards deep cover

caught at midwicket. Utseya leans forward to play the ball on the leg side and ends up lobbing it nice and slowly towards Ponting at midwicket. He has a hurt pinky but that was a ridiculously easy catch
Price pushes forward to play on the off side but gets beaten
driven off the front foot towards long on for one
played back to the bowler this time
dabbed off the back foot towards short third man
full ball angling away from the right-hander, the batsman has a waft but misses
good length just outside off stump, pushed from the crease towards point
short ball and the batsman pulls through square leg for one
Price tried to let that short of a length ball go but it hit him on the glove and flew over first slip's head towards third man
Cremer plays a nice-looking square drive but can't beat the fielder at point
short ball and Cremer lines up and pulls superbly all along the ground to the deep square leg boundary
the reverse-sweep from Price but he can't beat short third man
Price comes down the track and plays the ball towards mid-on
Cremer plays the ball towards long-on for one
down the track once again and swatted towards long-on
Cremer aims for long-on but plays it back to the bowler
played through square leg for a single
played off the back foot through point
good length on leg and middle, nudged from the crease towards midwicket
Price ducked straight into that short ball from Watson and got hit flush on the helmet. Why they allow leg byes for evasive action I don't know. Daft rule.

caught behind! Johnson slants a good length ball across Cremer, giving him some width. Cremer chases it, playing away from his body, and gets an edge which Haddin catches by diving low and to his right
full ball outside off stump which Mpofu dabs towards third man
defended on the leg side off the back foot
pushed on the off side on the front foot
Mpofu tries to defend but gets beaten
defended confidently with a straight bat
Mpofu gets beaten again outside off stump
pushed off the front foot towards cover
driven towards mid-off from the crease
Johnson sends down another fast bouncer, the batsmen ducks while leaving his bat up like a periscope
Price swings at a full and wide out and misses
short of a length delivery from round the wicket, Price wafts and misses
good length delivery angling into the batsman, defended with a straight bat towards the bowler
Johnson beats the bat again by pitching one around middle and off and slanting it away from the right-hander. Price tried to drive without moving his feet and missed
driven off the front foot towards mid-off
Tait aims for the yorker first up and Mpofu manages to get some bat on it and play the ball behind square
good length and on off and middle stump, Price stays in his crease and blocks
full toss on leg stump and Price flicks firmly towards deep square leg
Mpofu's headbutted the ball. He ducked low and right into the line of a short of a length delivery and gets a leg bye for it. Daft rule.
another short ball, Price ducks under it
played off the pads towards the leg side
Johnson goes round the wicket and bowls a full ball outside off. Mpofu chases and gets beaten

caught! And that's the end of the game. Johnson pitches one closer to the batsman around off stump and gets it to straighten ever so slightly. Mpofu pushes forward at it and gets an edge which Haddin takes pretty easily.
